The joint statement issued by Vice President Joe Biden and European Union High Representative Javier Solana expresses support for Bosnia and Herzegovina as a single state with two entities and for the Dayton Accords. They also express support for the aspirations of the people of Bosnia and Herzegovina to join European and Trans-Atlantic institutions. The statement highlights concerns about threats to the territorial integrity of Bosnia and Herzegovina, economic conditions, and the independence of judicial institutions. The statement emphasizes the importance of completing the objectives and conditions set by the Peace Implementation Council for NATO and EU membership. It mentions the need for progress by June and completion by October. The statement also mentions the potential benefits of EU and NATO membership, such as visa-free travel, increased trade and investments, and support for economic development. The United States and the EU express their commitment to supporting growth and reform in Bosnia and Herzegovina.